  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SAFE Communities: Security Actions for Everybody</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community members in 25 communities and police officers at the local level</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">SO1 &#x2013; Promote inclusive participation of people in defending their rights 
SO2 &#x2013; Support the strengthening of accountable and transparent police-citizen relations</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to create space for Liberians in four central counties to engage in regular discussions with LNP officers, and to ensure that beneficiaries have a clear understanding of their rights and the mechanisms through which they can seek to hold officers accountable for neglect and wrongdoing. On the other side, LNP officers will be given training in how to peacefully resolve conflicts and respect the rights of citizens, and to communicate with community members the budgetary and capacity restraints that may at times make it difficult for them to conduct their duties. Greater communication between stakeholders in the security sector, as well as a stronger flow of information are expected outputs based on the project activities. Project activities have been developed around three expected results: Citizens increase awareness about their rights and obligations and those of security and justice institutions including complaints mechanisms (ER1); Citizens analyse, monitor, report and address the security and justice situation in their communities (ER2); CSOs promote greater accountability and transparency in the security and justice sector (ER3).</narrative>
  </description>
